The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Bomb-on-flight call nets duo
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Bomb-on-flight call nets duo
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Two men were arrested in Arambagh, Hooghly, in connection with a hoax call to IndiGo warning the staff that a bomb would be planted on the airlines Calcutta-Mumbai flight.        
	Srikanta Pramanik, 31, was arrested on Saturday night and his cousin Shyamal Pramanik, 19, was picked up on Sunday morning by a team from Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport police station.        
	Police said IndiGos call centre in Gurgaon received a hoax call on August 18. The caller claimed he had been asked to plant a bomb on the airlines Calcutta-Mumbai flight on August 27 morning, said an officer of the police station.        
	The airline immediately alerted the police. An FIR was lodged and a copy was forwarded to the airport police station as the flight was to originate from the city, said an officer of IndiGo.        
	The cops traced the call to the cellphone of Srikanta, an Arambagh resident. On Sunday, a team from the police station arrested Srikanta in his house.        
	During interrogation, Srikanta allegedly said he had given the SIM card of his phone to his cousin Shyamal a couple of months back. Shyamal was picked up early on Sunday. Both have been released on bail.        
	The police said Srikanta had worked as an artisan in Delhi but left the job a few months back and returned to his village. The duo earn their living by farming.                                                                                                                                                          
